<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id83e8188c-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s4501"><num value="4501">§ 4501.</num><heading> Authority of executive agency</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">An executive agency may—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id83e8188d-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s4501/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> make advance, partial, progress or other payments under contracts for property or services made by the agency; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id83e8188e-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s4501/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> insert in solicitations for procurement of property or services a provision limiting to small business concerns advance or progress payments.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id83e8188f-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/350/s3">Pub. L. 111–350, § 3</ref>, <date date="2011-01-04">Jan. 4, 2011</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3790">124 Stat. 3790</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
